@karalabe I'm not sure how to interpret "a while back" or "these problems" -- it all seems to be just one problem, not several; they're all the same stack trace.  Someone else just posted a giant gist in bug #14800 (for this same issue) and its for `instance=Geth/v1.7.3-stable-4bb3c89d/linux-amd64/go1.7.3` 

I understand the current version is 1.8 ... I have not yet tried building from source; the latest deb packages seem to be for 1.7.3 ...

Based on the stack trace, the naive assumption is that the problem is in `consensus/ethash/algorithm.go` but that file hasn't changed since before May 2017, before these bug reports. Looking at that file, such a bug seems unlikely, so I have to conclude that the bug is elsewhere, e.g. some premature release of some lock in some other thread, causing `algorithm.go` to access invalid memory -- then, sure, if a race condition was recently fixed, that might just solve things.
